<L>__{exterior washington d.c. day}
<A>__{janet, fleury and grace walking the rows of seven foot bronze soldiers. street cart hotdogs from foil wrappers.}
<C>__{director grace}
<P>__{(to fleury)}
<D>__{i see the look in your eyes. that look is trouble: old school, play ground shit, vengeance...}
<C>__{ronald fleury}
<D>__{it's not vengeance.}
<C>__{director grace}
<D>__{it ain't justice. it's stronger. we've all been there. i have. vengeance is always dirty, ronnie.}
<C>__{ronald fleury}
<D>__{i just can't sit this out. i can't watch this not get dealt with. not again.}
<P>__{(a beat...)}
<D>__{know what my high school football coach used to say to me?}
<C>__{director grace}
<D>__{what?}
<C>__{ronald fleury}
<D>__{"hit something." all night long, coach bailey would scream "hit something." every play.}
<C>__{director grace}
<D>__{that's good coaching.}
<C>__{ronald fleury}
<D>__{i'm fixing to go hit something, boss. you with me?}
<C>__{director grace}
<D>__{how you gonna do it?}
<C>__{ronald fleury}
<D>__{the saudis covet good pr as much as their oil: 15 of 19 hijackers on 9 11 means most americans will never stop asking if that saudi oil is worth it. it's all about press.}
<C>__{director grace}
<D>__{few more moves and it's total war, ronnie. the only time treason is palatable is when it's done righteously and completely...}
<A>__{fleury digesting grace's words: moments pass. then he looks to janet.}
<C>__{janet mayes}
<D>__{oh, i'm in...not a question. i'm definitely going.}
